<title>GERMANY: Waigel welcomes lira in ERM, says aids credibility.</title>
<headline>Waigel welcomes lira in ERM, says aids credibility.</headline>
<dateline>BONN 1996-11-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>German Finance Minister Theo Waigel on Monday welcomed the re-entry of the lira to Europe's Exchange Rate Mechanism.</p>
<p>In a statement released in Bonn, Waigel said that the agreed central rate of 990 lire to the mark was in line with observed currency rate developments in financial markets.</p>
<p>&quot;The participation of Italy in the exchange rate mechanism strengthens the credibility of Italy's convergence policy in financial markets,&quot; he added.</p>
</text>
